EXTENDED OUTLOOK
THURSDAY TO SUNDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 062300 UTC
ON THURSDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS GREENLAND 1051 EXTENDS A RIDGE
SE TOWARDS THE UK. LOW PRESSURE 998 IS CENTRED ACROSS NORWAY AND A SECOND
LOW 993 IS SITUATED IN THE AZORES. THROUGH THURSDAY NIGHT AND FRIDAY THE
NORWEGIAN LOW FILLS AND DRIFTS SW INTO FORTIES AND THE AZORES LOW ALSO FILLS
AS IT DRIFTS OVER PORTUGAL AND INTO SPAIN HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS IN-SITU.
THE NORWEGIAN LOW CONTINUES TO FILL THROUGH SATURDAY AS IT CONTINUES TO MOV
S INTO DOGGER BEFORE LOOSING ITS IDENTITY COME SUNDAY AFTERNOON. AT THE SAME
TIME HIGH PRESSURE IN GREENLAND DECLINES SLTLY REDUCING ITS INFLUENCE ON
THE UK AND HIGH PRESSURE 1017 FORMS OVER SPAIN AND INTENSIFIES AS IT DRIFTS
INTO THE MEDITERRANEAN. ON SUNDAY A DEEP LOW 966 APPROACHES FITZROY AND
HIGH PRESSURE 1015 BEGINS TO FORM OVER FRANCE. OCCASIONAL STRG WINDS N OF
